HEADWORD: Cryohydrate
<hw>Cry`o*hy"drate</hw> <pr>(kr?`?-h?"dr?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>kry`os</grk> cold + E. <ets>hydrate</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance, as salt, ammonium chloride, etc.,
which crystallizes with water of crystallization only at low
temperatures, or below the freezing point of water.</def> <rj><au> F.
Guthrie.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cryolite</ent>⟦br⟧
